Aerial spraying of Staten Island; clarification
-----------------------------------------------
The aerial spraying of Staten Island was undertaken because there are many
marginal areas where ground ULV treatments cannot reach mosquitoes. Under
appropriate conditions (wind speed and temperature) aerial application of
insecticides usually results in a more uniform deposition of the
insecticide, in this instance Anvil 10 + 10. It's a physical thing.
--
Henry R. Rupp
<h.rupp@att.net>
